  Mr JOSH WILSON

 (
Fremantle
) (
19:50
):  I am glad, grateful and humble to have been re-elected as the member for Fremantle. It is a great privilege, and it brings with it a great responsibility. The trust placed in me as a representative will continue to shape my work, it will drive me forward and it is a trust I will strive to keep earning as I go. I'm looking forward to again pouring myself into the work of this parliament, and I'm rapt to share that task with my new old colleagues in this place, the member for Mayo and especially the members for Longman and Braddon. I'll share that work with an old and dear friend, the new, new member for Perth.
